---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { tr } from '../i18n/utils';

const locale = 'en' as const;
const t = tr(locale);

const updated = '2026-05-22';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="privacy · entrópica"
  description="what we collect on this site, why, and how to turn it off."
  locale={locale}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="site-wrap">
      <div class="eyebrow">{t('consent.eyebrow')}</div>
      <h1 class="hero-h">{t('privacy.title')}</h1>
      <p class="hero-lede">{t('privacy.lede')}</p>
      <div class="updated">// last updated · {updated}</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="body">
    <div class="site-wrap">
      <article class="prose">
        <h2>the short version</h2>
        <p>
          this site collects anonymous, aggregated traffic data through google analytics so we
          know which pages people actually use. that's it. we don't sell data, we don't run
          ads, we don't share information with third parties beyond what's listed below.
        </p>
        <p>
          if you decline analytics in the banner at the bottom of the page, none of it loads.
          you can change your mind at any time by clearing this site's storage in your browser
          (the banner will reappear on next visit).
        </p>

        <h2>what we collect, and why</h2>
        <h3>1. google analytics (gtag.js)</h3>
        <p>
          if you accept the consent banner, google analytics 4 records: page views, time on
          page, referring url, approximate geographic region (country, city), device type and
          browser, and a randomised visitor id so we can tell repeat visits from new ones. ip
          addresses are anonymised before storage. data is retained for 14 months. it sits on
          google's servers; their privacy notice applies in addition to this one (see
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">policies.google.com/privacy</a>).
        </p>
        <p>
          if you decline, no analytics cookies are stored and no identifiable data is sent. we
          still receive a "consent denied" ping so we can count a hit, but it carries no
          information that identifies you.
        </p>

        <h3>2. the contact form</h3>
        <p>
          when you submit the contact form, the data (name, email, optional company, project
          location, project type, message) is sent through formspree.io to
          info@entropica-lab.com. formspree retains the submission for the duration of our
          subscription. their privacy notice applies (see
          <a href="https://formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy</a>).
          we keep correspondence in our regular inbox for as long as it's relevant to the
          project, then delete it.
        </p>

        <h3>3. site hosting</h3>
        <p>
          the site is hosted on github pages. github stores standard web server logs (ip,
          timestamp, user-agent, requested url) for operational and security purposes. we do
          not have access to those logs. their privacy notice applies (see
          <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com/site-policy</a>).
        </p>

        <h2>what we don't do</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>we don't sell your data to anyone, ever.</li>
          <li>we don't show ads or use ad cookies.</li>
          <li>we don't use cross-site or cross-device tracking.</li>
          <li>we don't run remarketing pixels (facebook, linkedin, etc.).</li>
          <li>we don't use session recording or heatmap tools.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>your rights</h2>
        <p>
          you can ask us at any time what data we have about you, ask for it to be corrected
          or deleted, or withdraw consent. for the contact form, that means asking us to
          delete the email thread. for analytics, deleting your browser cookies for this site
          removes your visitor id; for a full deletion request against google's servers, see
          <a href="https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/9852570" target="_blank" rel="noopener">google's data deletion guide</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          write to <a href="mailto:info@entropica-lab.com">info@entropica-lab.com</a> with
          "privacy" in the subject line.
        </p>

        <h2>changes to this notice</h2>
        <p>
          we'll update the "last updated" date at the top if anything changes. material
          changes (adding a new third-party service, for instance) we'll also call out via the
          consent banner.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero { padding: 96px 0 48px; }
  .hero .eyebrow {
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    font-weight: 400;
    display: inline-block;
  }
  .hero-h {
    font-size: clamp(34px, 5vw, 60px);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    margin: 0 0 24px;
    font-weight: 300;
    max-width: 24ch;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .hero-lede {
    font-size: clamp(17px, 1.4vw, 19px);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--mute-on-paper);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin: 0 0 24px;
    font-weight: 400;
  }
  .updated {
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--mute-on-paper-2);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .body { padding: 32px 0 96px; }
  .prose { max-width: 64ch; }
  .prose h2 {
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 48px 0 16px;
  }
  .prose h3 {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: 32px 0 10px;
  }
  .prose p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    color: var(--ink-on-paper);
  }
  .prose ul {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-weight: 400;
    padding-left: 22px;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }
  .prose li { margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .prose a {
    color: inherit;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-on-paper-2);
  }
  .prose a:hover { color: var(--amber); border-bottom-color: var(--amber); }
</style>
